main event: A retired Army officer in San Antonio, Texas observed a large, unidentified object resembling a delta-wing aircraft on August 26, 1951.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10 seconds and was traveling at a very high speed and altitude.
The object was dark in color and did not make any sound.
The object was headed in a northeasterly direction (315 degrees) and did not deviate from its course.
The report was classified as 'Confidential' and was forwarded to the Commanding General of the 14th Air Force and the Air Material Command at Wright-Patterson AFB.
The report was initially unclassified but was later downgraded and declassified over time.
photographs: no, the report does not contain any photographs
